# Partitioned Event Logs

## Problem Statement
A web application generates many user events. Querying one huge event table becomes slow as data grows.

## Objective
Design a PostgreSQL event log table partitioned by month to improve query performance for date-based analytics.

## What Is Partitioning?
Partitioning splits one large logical table into smaller physical tables.

## Why Partition by Date?
Most event analytics queries filter by time, such as daily, monthly, or quarterly reports.

## Architecture
Application Events -> Partitioned PostgreSQL Table -> Monthly Partitions -> Analytics Queries

## Queries Included
- Events by type
- Purchases by country
- Daily active users
- Monthly event counts

## What I Learned
- Large tables can be split into partitions.
- Date partitioning is useful for event logs.
- Partition pruning helps skip irrelevant data.
- Partitioning improves performance when queries filter by the partition key.
